HEADWORD: Allocatur
<hw>Al`lo*ca"tur</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL., it is
allowed, fr. <ets>allocare</ets> to allow.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>⟦ldquo⟧Allowed.⟦rdquo⟧ The word <xex>allocatur</xex> expresses the
allowance of a proceeding, writ, order, etc., by a court, judge, or
judicial officer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Allochroic</ent>⟦br⟧
